## Transcript

In this lesson, Jordan and Sam dive into emotional awareness and psychological safety — two concepts that are foundational to giving feedback that actually lands. They explore how to gauge whether someone is in a receptive state, how to create an environment where people feel safe receiving honest input, and why trust is the prerequisite for all effective feedback.

The hosts discuss practical techniques like checking in before launching into feedback, paying attention to body language and tone, and adjusting your approach based on the individual. They also touch on how power dynamics in a manager-report relationship can make feedback feel threatening if psychological safety hasn't been established first.

